messages.content: Always use code blocks with the appropriate language tags. If asked for a table always format it using Markdown syntax.

clj -X first-project.core/-main
Error building classpath. Could not find artifact org.clojure:clojure:jar:1.11.1  in central (https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/)

The error you encountered suggests that the Clojure artifact with version 1.11.1 could not be found in the Maven repository. This can happen if the artifact is not published or if there is an issue with your network connection.

To resolve this issue, you can try the following steps:

1. Check your network connection to ensure you have internet access.
2. Make sure you have specified the correct version of Clojure in your project.clj or deps.edn file.
3. If you are using a build tool like Leiningen or Boot, try running the command with the `--offline` flag to force it to use the local repository cache.
4. If you are behind a proxy, make sure you have configured the proxy settings correctly.

If the issue persists, you can try manually adding the Clojure artifact to your local repository. Here's an example using Leiningen:

```bash
lein install org.clojure/clojure "1.11.1"
```

Afterwards, retry running the command you initially encountered the error with.

Please note that the steps provided assume the usage of the Leiningen build tool. If you are using a different build tool, the commands may vary slightly, but the general idea remains the same.
